# ReaMD .gitignore
# Goal: keep the public repo to clean code + ReaPack metadata + public docs/screenshots only.

# ─── OS / editor cruft ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ─── Local working state (never push) ──────────────────────────────────────
.claude/
thoughts/
.tldr/
.tldrignore
*.log
*.bak
*.backup
*.orig

# ─── Forum / draft / private notes ─────────────────────────────────────────
# We use docs/FORUM_*.txt locally as scratchpads for REAPER forum replies.
# They are not part of the published package.
docs/FORUM_POST.txt
docs/FORUM_POST_*.txt
docs/FORUM_UPDATE_*.txt
docs/DRAFT_*
docs/PRIVATE_*
docs/NOTES_*

# ─── AI Parse temp files (written to $TMPDIR, but in case any leak here) ──
*.request
*.response
*.sh.tmp
ai_parse_*.sh
ai_parse_*.bat
reamd_ai_response_*

# ─── Local config / secrets (paranoid catch-all) ───────────────────────────
# API keys are stored in REAPER ExtState, never in repo files. These patterns
# exist in case a user creates a side-config file by hand.
config.local.lua
*.secret
*.key
*.pem
.env
.env.*
